dcterms:creator: Yann LeCun
dcterms:description: The MNIST dataset is a collection of handwritten digits, widely used for training various image processing systems. It consists of 60,000 training images and 10,000 testing images of digits from 0 to 9.
dcterms:title: MNIST

dcterms:creator: Liu et al.
dcterms:description: CelebA is a large-scale face attributes dataset with more than 200,000 celebrity images, each annotated with 40 attribute labels. It is commonly used for training models in facial recognition and attribute prediction.
dcterms:title: CelebA
